    "Hussein et al. (2019) and Ke and Ng (2019) discussed AES models that leverage handcrafted features and neural network.",
    "Lagakis and Demetriadis (2021) and Ramesh and Sanampudi (2022) conducted a survey that extends the aforementioned survey papers to include transformer-based AES models.",
    "These works highlights the importance of simultaneously utilizing handcrafted features and automatically extracted features to enhance performance and generate immediate feedback.",
    "Chassab et al. (2021) discussed feature representation methods used in AES tasks.",
    "They presented a taxonomy of AES feature analysis methods, which are categorized into structure, frequency and term occurrence, semantic, and morphology feature analysis."
